Re: Unable to run shell script

    Quote Originally Posted by probono View Post
    Here is a somewhat hackish way to patch away the "showexec" option from the automounter:

    Code:

    sudo sed -i -e 's|showexec|\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00|g' /usr/lib/udisks/udisks-daemon

    CAUTION: Works for me after a reboot, but no guarantees. Make a backup before you do this!
    
    
    https://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=2321663


TRUECRYPT ERROR
stack overflow:


	

    selected the container to mount as usual clicking on the "Select file" button
    once selected the container file hit I clicked on the "Mount" button
    in the password input popup I clicked on the "Option" button
    in the full option popup I checked the radio box "Do no mount" in the filesystem frame at the bottom of the page
    type the password and clicked on the "Ok" button
    at the shell prompt I issued the following command: sudo ntfsfix /dev/mapper/truecrypt9 please note that the proper device depends on the slot selected for the container mount (truecrypt9 is for slot 9) and this was the output of the command:

Mounting volume... $MFTMirr does not match $MFT (record 0).

FAILED

Attempting to correct errors...

Processing $MFT and $MFTMirr...

Reading $MFT... OK

Reading $MFTMirr... OK

Comparing $MFTMirr to $MFT... FAILED

Correcting differences in $MFTMirr record 0...OK

Processing of $MFT and $MFTMirr completed successfully.

Setting required flags on partition... OK

